<subSubSection id="C35B6568377C3F1EFCD6F88F91D432CB" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="26" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377C3F1EFCD6F88F91D432CB" blockId="26.[835,1474,1795,2108]" lastBlockId="27.[813,1452,1671,1727]" lastPageId="27" lastPageNumber="136" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377C3F1FFCD6F88F91CB336F" bold="true" box="[835,957,1795,1819]" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Both sexes: body sub-ovate, ventral surface with distinct dark marks; fore femur clearly longer than mesosternum. Male: fore femur moderately slender (ratio length/width: 5.66–6.49), proximal half about as wide as distal half, ventral surface with a distinct notch near the middle, pilosity denser and longer at proximal half (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377C3F1FFA03F828910733A8" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="135">Fig. 108</figureCitation>
); genitalia of medium size, abdominal segment 8 clearly longer than sternum 7; pygophore simple, on ventral view apex of pygophore broadly rounded, postero-lateral surface with sparse long yellowish hairs; proctiger simple, slightly broadened at basal two-fifths, with long hairs on lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFEB1F92B93F232B4" box="[292,388,1703,1728]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 109</figureCitation>
); paramere not extending beyond genital segment but prominent, curved dorsad at distal half, apex broadened and rounded, curved outwards and posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFF60F88B93E23354" box="[245,404,1799,1824]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Figs. 110–112</figureCitation>
); endosoma: dorsal sclerite long and recurved proximally, apical accessory sclerite large but weakly sclerotised, lateral sclerite slender and short, thin accessory lateral sclerite present (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFE76F8EB90F333F4" box="[483,645,1895,1920]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Figs. 113, 114</figureCitation>
). Female: fore femur simple and slender (ratio length/width 6.94–7.53); hind trochanter elongated, without long hairs (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFDEAF82B909433CB" box="[639,738,1959,1983]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 115</figureCitation>
); abdomen shortened, tip of abdomen not surpassing apex of hind trochanter; sternum 7 large, clearly longer than previous sterna together, constricted laterally, posterior part producing a median lobe with broadly rounded apical margin, directed dorsad, and completely enclosing genitalia on ventral view (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFCA3F92B91E032CB" box="[822,918,1703,1727]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" captionTargetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" captionTargetId="figure-210@27.[97,1466,177,1533]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of Metrocoris monticola, new species. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Fig. 116</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF3E666B377D3F1EFFE4F98D910E3224" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502664" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4502664" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502664/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136" startId="27.[113,157,1537,1559]" targetBox="[115,1452,191,1521]" targetPageId="27">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377D3F1EFFE4F98D910E3224" blockId="27.[113,1452,1537,1616]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">
Figs. 108–116. Morphological features of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377D3F1EFD9DF98D90AF3262" authority="A.D. &amp; Polhemus, 2017" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[520,729,1537,1558]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="136" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377D3F1EFD9DF98D90AF3262" box="[520,729,1537,1558]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Metrocoris monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206578A377D3F1EFD70F98D912D3263" box="[741,859,1537,1559]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 108: right fore leg of male. 109: proctiger of male. 110–112: left paramere, three different views. 113, 114: endosomal sclerites, lateral and dorsal views. 115: hind coxa and trochanter of female. 116: sternum 7 of female, ventral view (110–114 same scale; 115, 116 same scale).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<subSubSection id="C35B6568377D3F19FCB8F96B93A83301" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="27" pageNumber="136" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377D3F1EFCB8F96B91A3332B" blockId="27.[813,1453,1767,1887]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377D3F1EFCB8F96B91B3328B" bold="true" box="[813,965,1767,1791]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Description.</emphasis>
Size: apterous males: length 5.80–6.00 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377D3F1EFCA1F88B91E5336B" box="[820,915,1799,1823]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">holotype</typeStatus>
5.88), width 2.53–2.75 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377D3F1EFB37F88B9777336B" box="[1186,1281,1799,1823]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">holotype</typeStatus>
2.66); apterous females, length 5.13–5.44 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377D3F1EFBC3F8AB96D8334B" box="[1110,1198,1831,1855]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">allotype</typeStatus>
5.13), width 2.75–2.84 (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377D3F1EFCA3F8CB91F8332B" box="[822,910,1863,1887]" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">allotype</typeStatus>
2.75).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377D3F19FCBAF80B906C3781" blockId="27.[811,1453,1927,2111]" lastBlockId="28.[134,777,189,1014]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="137" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">
Colour (
<figureCitation id="137A2A66377D3F1EFC13F80B967133D4" box="[902,1031,1927,1952]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[135,179,1936,1958]" captionTargetBox="[242,1379,246,1880]" captionTargetId="figure-7@6.[135,1473,189,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 18–31. Dorsal colour patterns of Metrocoris species. 18, 19: M. inthanon, specimens from Vietnam, Nghe An Prov., Pu Mat Nature Reserve (CL 4385). 20, 21: M. sicilis, new species, paratypes, from Vietnam, Hanoi, Ba Vi N’Park (CL 4393). 22, 23: M. triangulatus, specimens from Vietnam, Kontum Prov., 60 km NW. of Kontum (CL 4280). 24, 25: M. nigriventris, new species, paratypes, from Vietnam, Lai Chau Prov., 12 km N. of Lai Chau (CL 4410). 26, 27: M. monticola, new species, paratypes, from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., Sa Pa, Sin Chai (TAD1363). 28, 29: M. sapa, new species, paratypes, from Vietnam, Lao Cai Prov., Sa Pa, Nui Xe (TAD0416). 30, 31: M. tenuicornis, specimens from Vietnam, Gia Lai Prov., 60 km N. of An Khe (CL 4309)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4502642" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4502642/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="136">Figs. 26, 27</figureCitation>
): Apterous morph: Interocular area with dark brown mark medially. Antenna: segment 1 yellowish at proximal part and brown at distal part; segments 2–4 brown or lightly brown. Dorsum of thorax yellowish with black markings. Pronotum with median black T-shaped mark at anterior margin and confluent with two black marks on anterolateral areas, which run to propleura. Mesonotum: black mark on anterior margin connected with lateral stripes and median longitudinal stripe; lateral stripes slender, reaching posterior margin of mesonotum; sublateral marks slender broadened posteriorly, confluent with black mark on anterior margin; mesopleura with a longitudinal brown stripe. Metanotum with broad black mark running along anterior and lateral margins, confluent with medial longitudinal mark and metacetabular black marks, bordering yellowish background; metacetabula with broad black marks usually reaching posterior margin of metacetabula; yellow areas on meso- and metacetabula covered with silvery pubescence. Fore femur with apical dark ring and a distinct longitudinal mark on external side usually connected with ring, inner and ventral surface either dark brown or light brown; fore tibia and tarsus brown or dark brown. Middle and hind legs: coxae and trochanters chiefly yellowish; middle femur mostly yellow, dorsal surface with a longitudinal slender brown mark, ventral surface sometimes with indistinct longitudinal brown mark; hind femur only yellowish proximally; tibiae and tarsi dark brown. Abdomen mostly black dorsally. Venter of body with distinct dark marks: pro-, meso-, and metasternum with broad longitudinal black mark medially; mesosternum with addtional broad black or dark brown marks on antero-lateral and postero-lateral areas; abdominal sterna chiefly brown, terminal segments usually yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FF1DFB92938531C1" blockId="28.[134,777,1053,1461]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
Apterous male (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377A3F19FEB9FB9193F83041" box="[300,398,1053,1077]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">holotype</typeStatus>
): Head width 1.49, interocular width 0.67, eye size 0.64. Lengths of antennal segments 1–4: 2.81: 1.15: 0.95: 0.80. Pronotum length 0.55, mesonotum length 1.55. Lengths of leg segments (femur: tibia: tarsus 1: tarsus 2): fore leg: 2.72: 2.43: 0.14: 0.90; middle leg: 6.90: 4.85: 2.50: 0.41; hind leg: 7.00: 4.15: 0.35: 0.40. Fore femur: width 0.44, other characteristics as in Diagnosis above. Abdomen length on ventral view: 2.00, pregenital length 0.74; sternum 7 about as long as sterna 4–6 combined, length 0.27. Genital segments medium size: segment 8 not distinctly broadened posteriorly, length 0.58, width 0.81; characteristics of pygophore, proctiger, paramere, and endosoma as in Diagnosis above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FF1DFA5293FC3341" blockId="28.[134,775,1501,1845]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
Apterous female (
<typeStatus id="54FA8841377A3F19FEC4FA5193D93181" box="[337,431,1501,1525]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">allotype</typeStatus>
): Head width 1.42; interocular width 0.64; eye size 0.63. Lengths of antennal segments 1–4: 2.30: 1.05: 0.95: 0.79. Pronotum length 0.49, mesonotum length 1.59. Lengths of leg segments: fore leg: 2.56: 2.28: 0.09: 0.86; middle leg: 6.40: 4.45: 2.45: 0.40; hind leg: 6.40: 3.75: 0.39: 0.44. Fore femur simple and slender, width 0.34. Hind coxae simple, without apical projection, hind coxa and trochanter without long hairs, length of hind trochanter 0.68. Abdominal venter length 1.53, length of tergum 7: 0.09, length of sternum 7 (caudal view): 0.92; shape of sternum 7: see Diagnosis above.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FF1DF8D293A83301" blockId="28.[136,478,1885,1909]" box="[136,478,1885,1909]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">Macropterous morph unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B6568377A3F19FF1DF811967F31E1" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FF1DF81196A23761" blockId="28.[136,775,1949,2101]" lastBlockId="28.[834,1475,189,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FF1DF811928E33C1" bold="true" box="[136,248,1949,1973]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12377A3F19FE97F811938B33C1" author="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N" box="[258,509,1949,1973]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" pagination="45 - 82" refId="ref41516" refString="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I and Part II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 - 2): 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser (1993)</bibRefCitation>
defined the 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FD18F812917033C1" box="[653,774,1950,1973]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. compar</emphasis>
species group on the basis of the following character states: usually darkened ventral surface of the body; male fore femur slender and simple; male paramere hook-shaped or falciform; male endosoma with a long ventral sclerite; hind coxa and trochanter of female usually modified (e.g., elongated and covered with very long hairs); sternum 7 of female constricted, with a median lobe on posterior margin. Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FC14FE9296653541" authority="A.D. &amp; Polhemus, 2017" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[897,1043,285,309]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FC14FE9296653541" box="[897,1043,285,309]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206578A377A3F19FBB6FE9296D13541" box="[1059,1191,285,309]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FB74FE9297F23541" authority="A.D. &amp; Polhemus, 2017" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1249,1412,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB74FE9297F23541" box="[1249,1412,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206578A377A3F19FA03FE9291E63521" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
clearly belong to the 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBEDFEB2969A3521" box="[1144,1260,318,341]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. compar</emphasis>
species group. This new species is similar in many respects to 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FA8EFED297CD3501" authority="A.D. &amp; Polhemus, 2017" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1307,1467,350,373]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FA8EFED297CD3501" box="[1307,1467,350,373]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A206578A377A3F19FCD6FEF291BE35E1" box="[835,968,381,405]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but differs from the latter by the combination of the following characteristics: longer fore femur (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FA30FE1291DB35A1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FA30FE1291DB35A1" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly longer than the mesosternum in both sexes, while in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FC32FE52963F3581" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[935,1097,478,501]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FC32FE52963F3581" box="[935,1097,478,501]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only subequal to the length of the mesoternum); shape of the fore femur of the male (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FA30FE7291D83641" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FA30FE7291D83641" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the notch in the middle of the ventral surface more distinct); relatively larger genitalia; the shape of the male paramere; the shape of pygophore on ventral view; the pilosity of pygophore (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBC3FDF2969336E1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1110,1253,637,661]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBC3FDF2969336E1" box="[1110,1253,637,661]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with sparse hairs, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FCD1FD12919436C1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[836,994,670,693]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FCD1FD12919436C1" box="[836,994,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. nigriventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with longer and denser hairs); slightly longer abdomen in the female (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBFFFD32968C36A1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1130,1274,701,725]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBFFFD32968C36A1" box="[1130,1274,701,725]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly surpassing the apex of hind coxae); and the median lobe of sternum 7 of female (broader in 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBA3FD7296B23761" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1078,1220,765,789]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBA3FD7296B23761" box="[1078,1220,765,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FCD6FCB1967F31E1" blockId="28.[835,1476,829,1429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
The shape of paramere of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBCBFCB2969B3721" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1118,1261,829,853]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBCBFCB2969B3721" box="[1118,1261,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is relatively similar to that of 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FC2FFCD296E23701" box="[954,1172,862,885]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FC2FFCD296433701" box="[954,1077,862,885]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metrocoris</taxonomicName>
compar
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12377A3F19FB33FCD197403701" author="White FB" box="[1190,1334,861,885]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref42124" refString="White FB (1883) Report on the pelagic Hemiptera procured during the voyage of H. M. S. Challenger during the years 1873 - 1876. Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H. M. S. Challenger in the years 1873 - 1876, 7 (19): 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1883">White, 1883</bibRefCitation>
) from 
<collectingCountry id="F3567673377A3F19FA1CFCD197B73701" box="[1417,1473,861,885]" name="India" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">India</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3567673377A3F19FCE7FCF291AA37E2" box="[882,988,894,918]" name="Myanmar" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FB82FCF2977937E1" authority="Zettel, 2011" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2011" box="[1047,1295,893,917]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB82FCF296F337E1" box="[1047,1157,893,917]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. pardus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12377A3F19FB18FCF1977937E1" author="Zettel H" box="[1165,1295,893,917]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" pagination="109 - 114" refId="ref42232" refString="Zettel H (2011) Metrocoris pardus sp. n. (Heteroptera: Gerridae) aus Westmalaysien. Zeitschrift der Arbeitsgemeinschaft Osterreichischer Entomologen, 63 (2): 109 - 114." type="journal article" year="2011">Zettel, 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F3567673377A3F19FCD1FC1191DE37C1" box="[836,936,925,949]" name="Malaysia" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
, but other characters show significant differences between the these species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBF2FC32968137A1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1127,1271,957,981]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBF2FC32968137A1" box="[1127,1271,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FAB9FC3297ED37A1" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2011" box="[1324,1435,957,981]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FAB9FC3297ED37A1" box="[1324,1435,957,981]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. pardus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinctly different in the colour pattern of dorsum; and the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FC22FC72965F3061" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2011" box="[951,1065,1021,1045]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pardus">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FC22FC72965F3061" box="[951,1065,1021,1045]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. pardus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a distinctly shortened abdomen, with the apex of the abdomen only reaching the base of the hind coxa, while in the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FB26FBB297353021" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1203,1347,1085,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB26FBB297353021" box="[1203,1347,1085,1109]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the apex of the abdomen reaches the apex of the hind coxa. Comparing 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FCD1FBF291A430E1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[836,978,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FCD1FBF291A430E1" box="[836,978,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB91FBF2960F30E1" box="[1028,1145,1150,1173]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. compar</emphasis>
, the paramere of 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FAA1FBF297B430E1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1332,1474,1149,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FAA1FBF297B430E1" box="[1332,1474,1149,1173]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has no long hairs as seen in that of the latter; 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FAA1FB1297B230C1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1332,1476,1181,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FAA1FB1297B230C1" box="[1332,1476,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a longer sternum 7 (about 1.5 times as long as the preceeding abdominal sterna, versus only about 1.1 times in 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FCF5FB7291A33161" box="[864,981,1278,1301]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. compar</emphasis>
, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD04B12377A3F19FB9BFB71968E3161" author="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N" box="[1038,1272,1277,1301]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" pagination="45 - 82" refId="ref41516" refString="Chen PP &amp; Nieser N (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I and Part II. Steenstrupia, 19 (1 - 2): 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993</bibRefCitation>
). It is notable that, among taxa in the 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB84FA9296FE3141" box="[1041,1160,1310,1333]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. compar</emphasis>
species group, 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FAA1FA9297B23141" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1332,1476,1309,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FAA1FA9297B23141" box="[1332,1476,1309,1333]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">M. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has probably the simplest hind coxa and trochanter in the female, being elongated but without significant modification and no long hairs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B6568377A3F19FCD6FA3191803241" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FCD6FA3191803241" blockId="28.[835,1474,1469,1589]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FCD6FA3191BA31A1" bold="true" box="[835,972,1469,1493]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D60377A3F19FBC1FA3196B231A1" authorityName="A.D. &amp; Polhemus" authorityYear="2017" box="[1108,1220,1469,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FBC1FA3196B231A1" box="[1108,1220,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, treated as a noun in apposition, meaning inhabiting (- 
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FB46FA5197723181" box="[1235,1284,1501,1525]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">cola</emphasis>
) mountain area (
<emphasis id="B935EAF1377A3F19FCD8FA7291FB3261" box="[845,909,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">monti</emphasis>
-), is given to this species, as it was found in a montane stream.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35B6568377A3F19FCD0F9D1973E32A1" pageId="28" pageNumber="137" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFE36E3377A3F19FCD0F9D1976B3201" blockId="28.[837,1309,1629,1653]" box="[837,1309,1629,1653]" pageId="28" pageNumber="137">
